1
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:51,611
"In the world before,

2
00:01:51,678 --> 00:01:56,249
"the earth was covered with highways and buildings.

3
00:01:56,316 --> 00:02:01,855
"And it was a lone scientist who discovered a tiny speck in the night sky,

4
00:02:01,921 --> 00:02:05,859
and the land was changed forever."

5
00:02:05,925 --> 00:02:09,062
Miss Lowe, what happened then ?

6
00:02:43,429 --> 00:02:45,865
[ People Screaming ]

7
00:02:51,437 --> 00:02:53,373
[ All Screaming ]

8
00:03:37,517 --> 00:03:40,153
[ Electronic Beeping ]

9
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,991
[ Beeping Rapidly ]

10
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:50,463
Well, this is it. Menkees, welcome home. [ Chuckles ]

11
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:52,732
Doesn't look like much.

12
00:03:52,799 --> 00:03:54,968
Yeah.

13
00:03:55,034 --> 00:03:57,937
Well, use your imagination, boy.

14
00:03:58,004 --> 00:03:59,973
Gandry. Here ?

15
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:02,075
Right there, sir.

16
00:04:30,737 --> 00:04:34,474
Why do I feel like the bad guy ?

17
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:38,011
'Cause we're about to rat on our own government. What's the matter ?

18
00:04:38,077 --> 00:04:40,113
Feeling guilty, Stan ?

19
00:04:40,179 --> 00:04:42,115
No. You, partner ?

20
00:04:42,181 --> 00:04:45,084
I love when you call me that. Come on.

21
00:04:50,990 --> 00:04:53,259
[ Mechanical Hum ]

22
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:09,876
Up. Where you goin' ?

23
00:05:09,942 --> 00:05:12,045
Just get up.

24
00:05:38,371 --> 00:05:40,340
[ Shutter Clicking ]

25
00:05:53,419 --> 00:05:55,354
Let's see it.

26
00:06:04,130 --> 00:06:06,532
[ Beeping ]

27
00:06:10,336 --> 00:06:14,040
[ Beeping Continues ]

28
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:16,943
Satisfied ?

29
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:19,712
It'll do.

30
00:06:21,781 --> 00:06:24,050
[ Rustles ]

31
00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:26,886
- Freeze ! - Oh, boy.

32
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,589
Take care of him !

33
00:06:45,872 --> 00:06:48,407
My partner, the show-off. Where would you be without me ?

34
00:06:48,474 --> 00:06:51,911
At home with a book and a beer, thank you. [ Mechanical Hum ]

35
00:06:51,978 --> 00:06:54,313
Meet me back at the jeep.

36
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:57,116
Come on. Go, go, go, go !

37
00:06:57,183 --> 00:06:59,118
Move it.

38
00:07:19,338 --> 00:07:21,774
Uh... I-- I don't have a gun.

39
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,449
Stan. Don't move !

40
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:34,487
Sir. Jake Lowe, combat photographer.

41
00:07:34,554 --> 00:07:37,523
Combat nothing. Hit the ground.

42
00:07:37,590 --> 00:07:39,559
Now.

43
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:47,200
Your camera, soldier. Sorry. [ Groans ]

44
00:07:47,266 --> 00:07:51,270
I can't. It's a rental. I'll lose my deposit.

45
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:58,010
At peacetime, you guys will do just about anything to get a story.

46
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:21,434
Here you go, boss.

47
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,536
Thanks. [ Sighs ]

48
00:08:25,872 --> 00:08:30,743
You know, I haven't had a front page story since the... orangutan broke its silence.

49
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:33,946
- What was that, four years ago ? - Something like that, yeah.

50
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:37,183
[ Intercom Ringing ]

51
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,619
[ Clicks ] Jake.

52
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:43,022
[ Woman ] Mr. Shyler would like to see you in his office.

53
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:46,692
See ya.

54
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:49,328
Good luck.

55
00:08:49,395 --> 00:08:52,999
I don't know how to, uh--

56
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,236
These last few months, you--

57
00:08:57,303 --> 00:09:00,339
Well, you just haven't been producing the same material.

58
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:03,676
You're kidding, right ?

59
00:09:03,743 --> 00:09:07,179
I mean, this whole outfit is the same goddamn material. Jake,

60
00:09:07,246 --> 00:09:10,516
when you came here, we were lucky to have you.

61
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:13,686
But you have to remember we were the only ones who would take you...

62
00:09:13,753 --> 00:09:17,089
after your early... discharge.

63
00:09:17,156 --> 00:09:20,092
You make it sound like some embarrassing medical problem.

64
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:23,229
It's not that you're not a great reporter, because you are.

65
00:09:23,296 --> 00:09:26,532
It just that maybe your heart's someplace else.

66
00:09:26,599 --> 00:09:30,102
You know, you're right. So I'll tell you what.

67
00:09:30,169 --> 00:09:33,105
Why don't we just call this another one of those "early discharges,"

68
00:09:33,172 --> 00:09:36,042
only this time, I'm gonna walk on my own.

69
00:09:36,108 --> 00:09:38,611
Jake.

70
00:09:40,179 --> 00:09:42,748
Well, I think that went pretty well.

71
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:05,071
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

72
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:11,143
Hi. Hey.

73
00:10:11,210 --> 00:10:13,412
My uncle called.

74
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:17,917
He's got a position available in sales.

75
00:10:17,984 --> 00:10:20,920
It's not far from here. It's a good job.

76
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:25,257
It has great benefits and good hours.

77
00:10:25,324 --> 00:10:27,760
I quit my job.

78
00:10:27,827 --> 00:10:30,429
You quit ? That's great.

79
00:10:30,496 --> 00:10:32,932
It couldn't be better timing.

80
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:38,270
[ Sighs ] I don't want your uncle's job, Amy.

81
00:10:39,505 --> 00:10:41,874
[ Sighs ] Okay.

82
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:45,711
So what are you gonna do ? Another tabloid ?

83
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:50,049
You can't keep running after stories about aliens...

84
00:10:50,116 --> 00:10:52,551
and Jesus's face in a birthday cake.

85
00:10:52,618 --> 00:10:54,720
It's killing you.

86
00:10:54,787 --> 00:10:57,957
I just said I quit my job. I don't need another reality speech.

87
00:10:58,024 --> 00:10:59,792
[ Sighs ]

88
00:11:22,481 --> 00:11:25,484
[ Earth Rumbling ]

89
00:11:25,551 --> 00:11:27,520
[ Rumbling Fades ]

90
00:11:31,157 --> 00:11:33,793
[ Phone Ringing ]

91
00:11:37,096 --> 00:11:39,265
Hello ? [ Stan ] Jake ?

92
00:11:39,331 --> 00:11:42,735
Jake, it's me, partner. Stan ?

93
00:11:42,802 --> 00:11:44,870
[ Jake ] Jesus, you're alive !

94
00:11:44,937 --> 00:11:48,040
[ Stan ] The one and only. Get a pen.

95
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:51,444
Fifteen degrees longitude,

96
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:53,446
six degrees latitude.

97
00:11:53,512 --> 00:11:57,383
West northwest. The Sierras.

98
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:59,885
S-Stan, are you okay ? Are you safe ?

99
00:11:59,952 --> 00:12:05,424
We'll talk later. Just know this is our "last dance."

100
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:08,360
A stranger will contact you.

101
00:12:08,427 --> 00:12:11,063
He'll have something you'll need.

102
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:15,000
Be his friend. You understand ? Be his friend.

103
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:17,336
[ Clicks, Dial Tone ] S-Stan.

104
00:12:25,711 --> 00:12:27,780
I got a lead on a story.

105
00:12:27,847 --> 00:12:31,083
-It's a big story that could put this paper through the roof. -No, Jake.

106
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:35,087
No. No more shadow conspiracies, secret government enclaves.

107
00:12:35,154 --> 00:12:38,424
I need alien abductions ! It's not like that.

108
00:12:38,491 --> 00:12:42,128
This is "Last Dance." "Last Dance" ? What is that, a disco song ?

109
00:12:42,194 --> 00:12:44,396
It's not a joke ! Stan Alton and I--

110
00:12:44,463 --> 00:12:46,665
Wait. Stan Alton ? Isn't he dead ?

111
00:12:48,501 --> 00:12:50,936
I spoke to him on the phone last night.

112
00:12:51,003 --> 00:12:53,606
Oh, for Christ's sake, Jake !

113
00:12:53,672 --> 00:12:57,810
- This is a bona fide lead. I need an advance. - You've gotta be kiddin' me !

114
00:12:57,877 --> 00:13:01,280
You give me the advance, and the story is yours.

115
00:13:01,347 --> 00:13:04,984
- I thought you didn't work here anymore. - Earl,

116
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:07,720
this story is the reason I was discharged.

117
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,788
Do you want it or not ?

118
00:13:12,558 --> 00:13:15,528
[ Rumbling ]

119
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:40,085
Richter reports another seismic event.

120
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:43,389
This one originating in Naratake, northeast Asia.

121
00:13:43,455 --> 00:13:47,693
A 3.7. Avalanche this time. They're getting bigger.

122
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:51,030
Strange. I wouldn't have expected any tectonic activity...

123
00:13:51,096 --> 00:13:53,032
in that area.

124
00:13:53,098 --> 00:13:55,668
And certainly not this early. Yeah.

125
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:58,037
Maybe the planet's trying to tell us something.

126
00:13:58,103 --> 00:14:00,039
Nothing we don't already know.

127
00:14:00,105 --> 00:14:01,974
How's our rock doing ?

128
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,376
Tycus is approaching quadrant four radius.

129
00:14:04,443 --> 00:14:06,445
Trajectory, north.

130
00:14:08,881 --> 00:14:13,652
Just a few days, a couple of weeks at most, I promise.

131
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:17,223
I'm serious, Jake. This is it. You know--

132
00:14:17,289 --> 00:14:20,559
Amy, this is Stan. I left him behind once.

133
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:23,395
I can't do it again. [ Doorbell Rings ]

134
00:14:23,462 --> 00:14:26,098
Oh, but once again you'll leave me.

135
00:14:26,165 --> 00:14:29,668
What if something happens ? You've been thrown in a Mexican jail for months.

136
00:14:29,735 --> 00:14:32,571
You had to hide for six weeks in a Peruvian mountain.

137
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:34,573
[ Groans ]

138
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,575
You Jake Lowe ? Yeah.

139
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:40,813
Who the hell are you ? A friend, Mr. Lowe. I'm your friend.

140
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:49,722
You'll need these. What are they ?

141
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:53,525
Fake I.D. Thumbprint overlay.

142
00:14:53,592 --> 00:14:55,728
You're Fred Johnson.

143
00:14:55,794 --> 00:14:58,130
Fred ?

144
00:14:59,698 --> 00:15:02,568
Find the north tunnel, then go to the blue level.

145
00:15:02,635 --> 00:15:06,639
If anyone asks, you're with C-22 division.

146
00:15:08,007 --> 00:15:11,043
I guess that's about it. Wait.

147
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:14,880
Wait. What's going on ? I mean, where's Stan ? Is he okay ?

148
00:15:17,182 --> 00:15:20,452
I'm sorry. I can't answer that.

149
00:15:29,128 --> 00:15:31,063
Good-bye.

150
00:15:34,466 --> 00:15:37,336
I have to do this.

151
00:15:37,403 --> 00:15:40,172
You know I have to. Yeah.

152
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,644
Thanks.

153
00:15:52,384 --> 00:15:55,454
Jake ? [ Door Closes ]

154
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:05,130
Hey, boss. Hey, hey !

155
00:16:05,197 --> 00:16:07,866
Watch the leather, will ya ?

156
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:11,036
You okay ? Yeah.

157
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:13,205
Are you sure ?

158
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:19,144
I don't know. Let's go.

159
00:16:19,211 --> 00:16:21,213
[ Ignition Starts ]

160
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:26,552
[ Wind Chimes Chiming ] [ Car Approaching ]

161
00:16:36,862 --> 00:16:39,765
So where are you going anyway ?

162
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:43,535
I don't know. I'll tell you when I get back.

163
00:16:46,705 --> 00:16:49,908
Hey, Sam ? Keep an eye on Amy, will you ?

164
00:16:49,975 --> 00:16:52,745
Sure thing.

165
00:17:01,787 --> 00:17:03,789
[ Man ] Desert Storm--

166
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:06,024
[ Coughing ]

167
00:17:09,661 --> 00:17:12,531
Ah !

168
00:17:12,598 --> 00:17:14,900
Persian Gulf. You were there.

169
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:17,669
Am I right ? As a matter of fact, I was.

170
00:17:17,736 --> 00:17:19,271
[ Chuckling ]

171
00:17:19,338 --> 00:17:21,707
I'm looking for Commander Scott.

172
00:17:21,774 --> 00:17:23,742
Found him.

173
00:17:23,809 --> 00:17:28,080
I'm Jake Lowe. Pleased to meet ya. [ Grunts ]

174
00:17:28,147 --> 00:17:31,150
Ah ! Ah !

175
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:34,620
[ Groans, Grunts ] You ready to go ?

176
00:17:34,686 --> 00:17:36,955
Whenever you say, Commander.

177
00:17:37,022 --> 00:17:39,725
[ Chuckling, Groaning ]

178
00:17:42,628 --> 00:17:45,664
[ Sniffles ] It must be the rockin' motion.

179
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:49,968
It's the only place I can comfortably nod off.

180
00:17:50,035 --> 00:17:53,705
Okay. One-way ticket to the Sierras gonna cost you about...

181
00:17:53,772 --> 00:17:57,776
$285.50, paid up front, of course.

182
00:17:57,843 --> 00:18:00,012
Of course.

183
00:18:08,554 --> 00:18:11,557
- It's 300. - Three hundred ?

184
00:18:11,623 --> 00:18:14,893
- Flight insurance. - You're gonna need it.

185
00:18:17,529 --> 00:18:21,166
Okay, well, let's, uh... get this show on the road.

186
00:18:30,676 --> 00:18:33,045
Ah ! [ Sniffles ]

187
00:18:33,111 --> 00:18:36,114
So what's up here in the Sierras anyway ?

188
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:39,251
I don't know.

189
00:18:39,318 --> 00:18:42,521
Oh, top secret. I like it like that.

190
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:44,690
No, I really don't know.

191
00:18:44,756 --> 00:18:48,994
Well, if you don't know and I don't know, this oughta be fun !

192
00:18:49,061 --> 00:18:51,363
[ Laughing ]

193
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:55,701
If you want to go in the back and check your chute, go ahead.

194
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:58,437
You have jumped before, right ?

195
00:18:58,504 --> 00:19:02,140
Yeah, in the service. I hated it.

196
00:19:02,207 --> 00:19:04,877
Army, huh ?

197
00:19:04,943 --> 00:19:07,579
I knew you were a soldier. Was.

198
00:19:07,646 --> 00:19:10,716
Two years Force Recon Five Combat Camera.

199
00:19:10,782 --> 00:19:13,719
Combat Camera ? You guys are nuts !

200
00:19:13,785 --> 00:19:15,454
[ Laughing ]

201
00:19:18,957 --> 00:19:21,326
[ Coughing ]

202
00:19:24,129 --> 00:19:26,064
Oh... sorry.

203
00:19:26,131 --> 00:19:28,967
You gonna be all right if I go in the back ?

204
00:19:29,034 --> 00:19:31,737
Be all right ? Yeah, I'll be all right.

205
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:35,774
I think I got the instructions on how to fly this crate somewhere.

206
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,952
[ Man ] 1-800-TALK-CHEAP.

207
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:50,122
We're discussing the weird, wacky seismic activity that's been happening.

208
00:19:50,188 --> 00:19:52,457
Jerry in Canyon Country, you're on the air.

209
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:55,861
[ Jerry ] I think the planet is really trying to tell us something.

210
00:19:55,928 --> 00:19:57,863
Volcanic, tectonic, you name it.

211
00:19:57,930 --> 00:20:00,365
She's pissed off, man. [ Knock At Door ]

212
00:20:00,432 --> 00:20:02,200
[ Shyler ] What's that ?

213
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:05,871
Jake wanted to make sure you got that ahead of deadline.

214
00:20:10,642 --> 00:20:14,079
Now, that's a good story. Put it on page two.

215
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:15,981
All right.

216
00:20:18,984 --> 00:20:20,919
[ Jake ] Aren't we a little low ?

217
00:20:20,986 --> 00:20:23,021
Have to be.

218
00:20:23,088 --> 00:20:26,725
Get any lower, I won't need this chute. I can use a skateboard.

219
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:31,229
Well, I gotta be above ground level but below radar level.

220
00:20:31,296 --> 00:20:33,665
Radar ? Yeah, radar.

221
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:36,802
These days even dime bag dealers got radar.

222
00:20:36,868 --> 00:20:38,804
All you need's a truck.

223
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,576
How we doin' ?

224
00:20:44,643 --> 00:20:47,079
Closin' in on your coordinates.

225
00:20:50,315 --> 00:20:52,751
[ Scott ] All right. This must be the place.

226
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:56,254
Go time is marked-- 30 seconds.

227
00:20:58,690 --> 00:21:02,127
Thanks a lot, Commander. I'll buy you a drink sometime.

228
00:21:02,194 --> 00:21:04,696
Fifteen. A drink ? Cheapskate.

229
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:07,032
Well, you know where to find me.

230
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,534
Ten seconds. Good luck, soldier.

231
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,703
Yes, sir !

232
00:21:39,364 --> 00:21:42,367
[ Groaning ]

233
00:21:56,915 --> 00:21:59,751
[ Woman ] Seismologists are baffled at the sudden increase...

234
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:02,654
in seismic activity around the world.

235
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:05,390
Sizeable earthquakes have been reported in Peru, the United States...

236
00:22:05,457 --> 00:22:07,926
and the former Soviet Union.

237
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:11,563
Though many scientific sources have speculated on this unusual chain of events,

238
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:14,833
no cohesive theories have been introduced as of yet.

239
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:17,402
Meanwhile, an outbreak of forest fires...

240
00:22:17,469 --> 00:22:22,140
has smoke-jumpers pulling double duty in Idaho, south of the Sawtooth mountain range.

241
00:22:22,207 --> 00:22:25,877
The fire reportedly broke out spontaneously at an empty campground.

242
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:32,084
Tycus is really screwing with Mother Nature.

243
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:35,320
We've known for years the effects this thing would have on the solar system.

244
00:22:35,387 --> 00:22:37,556
What'd you expect ? Nothing.

245
00:22:37,622 --> 00:22:41,059
Just hoping for a change in course maybe.

246
00:22:41,126 --> 00:22:43,061
No, don't count on it.

247
00:22:43,128 --> 00:22:45,564
If there was, we'd know about it first.

248
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:48,834
Even Uncle Sam doesn't have tracking equipment this sensitive.

249
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:51,436
Start triangulation sequence. Check.

250
00:22:51,503 --> 00:22:54,072
[ Beeping ]

251
00:22:56,007 --> 00:22:58,343
Position locked, sir.

252
00:22:58,410 --> 00:23:00,278
Heading ?

253
00:23:00,345 --> 00:23:03,782
Tycus has just entered quadrant two radius.

254
00:23:03,849 --> 00:23:06,785
Velocity up eight percent.

255
00:23:06,852 --> 00:23:09,020
That's impossible.

256
00:23:09,087 --> 00:23:11,389
She's ahead of schedule, sir.

257
00:23:11,456 --> 00:23:13,225
[ Typing At Keyboard ]

258
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:15,727
What's its frigging hurry ?

259
00:23:15,794 --> 00:23:18,096
[ Typing ]

260
00:23:18,163 --> 00:23:20,632
[ Phone Ringing ] [ Touch Tone Dialing ]

261
00:23:33,879 --> 00:23:36,248
[ Grunts ]

262
00:23:49,194 --> 00:23:52,430
What the hell are you doing ?

263
00:23:52,497 --> 00:23:55,033
You were expected at the north tunnel ten minutes ago.

264
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:58,370
- Who are you ? - Johnson.

265
00:24:00,138 --> 00:24:02,040
C-22 division.

266
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:05,610
I'm sorry, sir. I, um--

267
00:24:05,677 --> 00:24:08,947
I had an accident. Never mind. Let's just get this where it's going.

268
00:24:37,042 --> 00:24:38,910
Hey, what are you doing up here ?

269
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:42,347
I'm late. Take it back down to the lower warehouse.

270
00:24:42,414 --> 00:24:46,485
We ain't gonna open up until later today. There's a systems test.

271
00:24:46,551 --> 00:24:48,753
All right. [ Ignition Starts ]

272
00:25:37,435 --> 00:25:39,371
You got it ?

273
00:25:39,437 --> 00:25:42,574
Just make sure you get a grip before we-- Mm-hmm.

274
00:25:42,641 --> 00:25:44,643
Hold on. Hey, hey, hey.

275
00:25:44,709 --> 00:25:47,779
Whoa, whoa !

276
00:25:47,846 --> 00:25:49,748
[ Sighs ]

277
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:56,388
All right. I thought you had it.

278
00:25:58,456 --> 00:26:01,693
[ Man On P.A. ] All shipments must be recorded in the receiving office.

279
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:05,096
Amtorg 12, report to security scanner.

280
00:26:05,163 --> 00:26:07,098
Code four.

281
00:26:12,604 --> 00:26:14,773
Handling, call holding on line two.

282
00:26:14,839 --> 00:26:17,008
Handling, line two.

283
00:26:17,075 --> 00:26:19,844
Stevens, Bogey in the warehouse.

284
00:26:21,479 --> 00:26:24,683
Amtorg 35, pick up at west loading dock.

285
00:26:24,749 --> 00:26:26,851
Amtorg 35.

286
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:30,188
[ Cocks Hammer ] Hold it right there, pal.

287
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:34,526
Whoa. Easy.

288
00:26:41,299 --> 00:26:43,335
Good afternoon.

289
00:26:43,401 --> 00:26:45,403
Fred. Fred Johnson.

290
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:48,540
Randall Barnet, Amtorg Mining Company.

291
00:26:48,606 --> 00:26:52,143
Do you understand that you've been trespassing on private property ?

292
00:26:52,210 --> 00:26:57,282
Gee, I didn't know. I was out hiking, and I got a little lost.

293
00:26:57,349 --> 00:27:00,986
Hiking, huh ? Where'd you get this ?

294
00:27:01,052 --> 00:27:04,155
[ Unzipping ]

295
00:27:04,222 --> 00:27:08,560
Ten cereal box tops. It comes with a decoder ring.

296
00:27:08,626 --> 00:27:10,695
Funny.

297
00:27:13,264 --> 00:27:15,233
Look, uh, Mr. Lowe,

298
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:19,404
we can do this the hard way or the really hard way.

299
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:21,773
Now, I'm gonna give you a break.

300
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:25,176
But first, I'm gonna keep the camera, the notebook--

301
00:27:25,243 --> 00:27:29,147
Oh, and this fancy global positioning system.

302
00:27:29,214 --> 00:27:32,083
Why don't you keep the candy bar too ?

303
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:35,320
And I want you to get the hell out of my operation and stay out.

304
00:27:35,387 --> 00:27:39,524
You got it ? What exactly are you mining here ?

305
00:27:39,591 --> 00:27:41,993
Uh, Stevens,

306
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:45,030
please help Mr. Lowe find his way home.

307
00:27:45,096 --> 00:27:47,732
He appears to be very lost.

308
00:27:51,136 --> 00:27:53,738
Oh, thanks for the gifts, Fred.

309
00:27:55,573 --> 00:27:59,744
Special Services, phone call on line 12. Special Services.

310
00:28:04,649 --> 00:28:07,619
Where the hell are we goin' ?

311
00:28:11,623 --> 00:28:14,526
You know Stan Alton ?

312
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:18,930
Boy, you just don't shut up, huh ?

313
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:43,955
[ Stevens Panting ]

314
00:28:54,165 --> 00:28:56,534
Road rage.

315
00:29:02,307 --> 00:29:04,309
[ Screaming, Shouting ]

316
00:29:17,889 --> 00:29:21,359
Tycus has just entered quadrant one, sir.

317
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:24,362
Won't be long before the whole world knows now.

318
00:29:24,429 --> 00:29:26,531
I can't believe we've known this long.

319
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:29,033
Deep pockets equal state-of-the-art equipment.

320
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:32,203
No government can touch what we've got going on here.

321
00:29:32,270 --> 00:29:35,840
I'm glad our families won't be on the surface when they find out.

322
00:29:35,907 --> 00:29:39,844
- Do you think there'll be a lot of panicking ? - Without a doubt.

323
00:29:39,911 --> 00:29:42,147
If you drove a bus every day of your life and found out...

324
00:29:42,213 --> 00:29:44,382
you had less than a month before you were toast, you think you'd show up...

325
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:46,217
for work the next day ?

326
00:29:46,284 --> 00:29:49,154
Not me, pal. Turn that up a second.

327
00:29:50,588 --> 00:29:52,857
...a convenience store on the outskirts of Blue Ridge...

328
00:29:52,924 --> 00:29:56,327
where the dormant Blue Ridge volcano has suddenly erupted without warning.

329
00:29:56,394 --> 00:29:59,130
Local authorities have begun emergency evacuation procedures,

330
00:29:59,197 --> 00:30:02,367
as lava and ash make their way to the center of town.

331
00:30:02,433 --> 00:30:04,736
Scientists are at a loss to explain the sudden explosion...

332
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:07,672
of volcanic activity in the West Coast.

333
00:30:07,739 --> 00:30:10,975
This is coming on the heels of a devastating storm front on the East Coast.

334
00:30:11,042 --> 00:30:13,378
We're getting hit on both sides of the continent.

335
00:30:13,444 --> 00:30:16,214
Not a good month to take a vacation.

336
00:30:24,122 --> 00:30:27,025
[ Sighs ]

337
00:30:34,566 --> 00:30:36,367
We're shut down. Systems test.

338
00:30:36,434 --> 00:30:40,138
I got orders to get this inside. Blue level. Right away.

339
00:30:40,205 --> 00:30:43,508
Blue level ? Let me see your I.D.

340
00:30:46,511 --> 00:30:48,880
Well, you ain't on my list.

341
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:52,851
Look, asshole,

342
00:30:52,917 --> 00:30:56,621
I got orders to get this inside from Barnet today.

343
00:30:56,688 --> 00:30:59,023
C-22 division.

344
00:31:01,559 --> 00:31:05,396
Oh. Hey, open it up !

345
00:31:05,463 --> 00:31:08,366
Have a good day. Thank you.

346
00:31:58,483 --> 00:32:02,453
[ Woman Over P.A. ] Technical supervisors, report to debriefing...

347
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:05,390
immediately following system test.

348
00:32:05,456 --> 00:32:09,160
Tycus E.T.A.: 40 minutes and counting.

349
00:32:23,374 --> 00:32:26,811
Supply manager to level eight admitting.

350
00:32:26,878 --> 00:32:29,914
Supply manager to level eight admitting.

351
00:32:37,221 --> 00:32:40,792
Amtorg 55, dial 3358.

352
00:32:40,858 --> 00:32:44,796
Amtorg 55, dial 3358.

353
00:32:52,437 --> 00:32:57,208
[ Man Clears Throat ] Everybody's immediate family members are here, sir.

354
00:32:57,275 --> 00:32:59,711
Don't you think you should make the call ?

355
00:32:59,777 --> 00:33:01,813
A little longer, Menkees.

356
00:33:03,581 --> 00:33:05,817
Pete, I understand your thinking,

357
00:33:07,452 --> 00:33:10,154
but Helen and Jamie should be here by now.

358
00:33:10,221 --> 00:33:13,991
You can't protect her from the truth forever.

359
00:33:14,058 --> 00:33:16,494
A few more days,

360
00:33:16,561 --> 00:33:19,163
another week of normal life.

361
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:21,599
I owe them that much. Okay.

362
00:33:23,234 --> 00:33:27,171
But for the record, I think you're cutting it too close.

363
00:33:27,238 --> 00:33:29,207
Noted, Menkees. Is that all ?

364
00:33:30,441 --> 00:33:32,944
Things will happen quickly when they happen.

365
00:33:47,091 --> 00:33:49,327
[ Sobbing ]

366
00:34:00,938 --> 00:34:02,907
[ Sniffles ]

367
00:34:02,974 --> 00:34:05,777
Hey.

368
00:34:10,782 --> 00:34:15,920
- [ Whispers ] Do you want to get out of here ? - Who are you ?

369
00:34:15,987 --> 00:34:18,389
I can help you.

370
00:34:20,858 --> 00:34:23,661
Guard ! Guard !

371
00:34:29,534 --> 00:34:32,203
[ Cocks Hammer ]

372
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:40,678
[ Kung Fu Yells ]

373
00:34:42,513 --> 00:34:44,816
[ Yelling Continues ]

374
00:34:48,653 --> 00:34:50,855
- Oh, no. - Oh ?

375
00:34:59,397 --> 00:35:02,200
You gotta start watching American movies, pal.

376
00:35:11,843 --> 00:35:13,878
Munson, you broke the rule.

377
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:16,280
We have limited space here.

378
00:35:18,449 --> 00:35:22,220
You know how difficult this is for me, Munson ?

379
00:35:22,286 --> 00:35:25,323
But unfortunately,

380
00:35:25,389 --> 00:35:28,793
you leave me no choice.

381
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:32,864
Don't do this. You're making a mistake.

382
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:37,401
You could have lived, and that's more than many could have even asked for.

383
00:35:37,468 --> 00:35:41,339
I'm not the only one. You know that.

384
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:43,574
Who's with you, Munson ?

385
00:35:44,609 --> 00:35:47,044
Answer him.

386
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:53,584
I am deeply troubled... that you force me to do this.

387
00:35:53,651 --> 00:35:57,088
Burn in hell.

388
00:35:57,154 --> 00:35:59,490
It'll be painless, I assure you.

389
00:35:59,557 --> 00:36:02,326
[ Groans ]

390
00:36:06,697 --> 00:36:09,567
[ Screams ]

391
00:36:13,571 --> 00:36:15,907
[ Gun Clatters Onto Floor ]

392
00:36:20,845 --> 00:36:25,950
We've gotta find the others. We just can't afford not to.

393
00:36:26,017 --> 00:36:28,119
Yes, sir.

394
00:36:32,890 --> 00:36:35,860
This is Menkees.

395
00:36:35,927 --> 00:36:38,963
I want a full level security sweep of this entire installation.

396
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:42,600
I want every crack in the floor checked.

397
00:36:42,667 --> 00:36:44,769
[ Radio Squelches ]

398
00:36:44,835 --> 00:36:47,939
Get rid of this body.

399
00:36:53,144 --> 00:36:55,580
There's something you see every day.

400
00:36:55,646 --> 00:36:58,816
[ Woman Over P.A. ] Orientation for red level personnel...

401
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:01,218
will commence at 0800 hours.

402
00:37:07,992 --> 00:37:11,829
Tycus E.T.A.: 30 minutes and counting.

403
00:37:19,804 --> 00:37:22,173
[ Beeping ]

404
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:37,321
[ Door Closes ]

405
00:37:48,733 --> 00:37:50,835
[ Electronic Beeping ]

406
00:38:07,918 --> 00:38:11,422
[ Grunts ] Hey, did you know they killed Munson ?

407
00:38:11,489 --> 00:38:15,092
They couldn't flip him. He didn't give up one name.

408
00:38:15,159 --> 00:38:19,330
He had balls. I'll say that much for him. Yeah, boy.

409
00:38:50,695 --> 00:38:53,364
Hey, what's Tycus' E.T.A. ? On schedule.

410
00:38:53,431 --> 00:38:57,001
That's why Crawford's getting nervous. He's not ready, and he knows it.

411
00:38:57,068 --> 00:38:59,870
Oh, how does that bastard sleep at night ?

412
00:38:59,937 --> 00:39:03,507
Pretty good. Have you seen his suite ? I'm not cleared for that floor.

413
00:39:03,574 --> 00:39:05,943
It's nicer than my apartment back home.

414
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:09,280
Forget about it. This is your home now. Oh.

415
00:39:09,346 --> 00:39:11,415
What took you so long ? Uh--

416
00:39:14,985 --> 00:39:16,987
We had trouble--

417
00:39:17,054 --> 00:39:20,191
It's working. Connie. Connie, it's me.

418
00:39:20,257 --> 00:39:23,427
I know. I'm trying.

419
00:39:23,494 --> 00:39:26,297
We're doing everything we can, believe me.

420
00:39:28,999 --> 00:39:31,268
Have you told the kids ?

421
00:39:31,335 --> 00:39:35,239
You gotta tell 'em. It's time. And tell 'em I--

422
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:38,275
Connie. Connie. [ Line Squeals ]

423
00:39:40,511 --> 00:39:43,147
Shit !

424
00:39:46,617 --> 00:39:49,386
We gotta move everything forward. Gandry, you got the numbers ?

425
00:39:49,453 --> 00:39:51,722
Most of 'em. Phillers, you talk to the pilot ?

426
00:39:51,789 --> 00:39:56,227
- Everyone's accounted for. - Business as usual till I give the go ahead.

427
00:39:56,293 --> 00:39:59,230
And let me handle Crawford. Let's go.

428
00:40:13,410 --> 00:40:15,913
[ Touch Tone Dialing ]

429
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:22,186
[ Phone Ringing ]

430
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:24,588
[ Beeps ] Hello.

431
00:40:24,655 --> 00:40:27,024
[ Jake ] Amy.

432
00:40:27,091 --> 00:40:29,794
Hi, Jake.

433
00:40:29,860 --> 00:40:32,596
Look, don't-- don't hang up.

434
00:40:32,663 --> 00:40:35,132
[ Sighs ] Give me one good reason.

435
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:39,370
I'm sorry about the way I left. I'm... sorry.

436
00:40:45,442 --> 00:40:48,512
I'm pregnant.

437
00:40:51,415 --> 00:40:53,684
Jesus.

438
00:40:53,751 --> 00:40:55,986
Why didn't you tell me this ?

439
00:40:56,053 --> 00:40:59,423
Oh, I don't know. It just didn't seem like the time.

440
00:40:59,490 --> 00:41:01,525
[ Sighs ]

441
00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:06,530
You don't have to come back, okay, until you're done.

442
00:41:07,965 --> 00:41:10,801
I love you.

443
00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:20,811
Things are weird here.

444
00:41:20,878 --> 00:41:23,914
[ Sighs ] The sky...

445
00:41:25,950 --> 00:41:29,486
burns different colors at noon.

446
00:41:29,553 --> 00:41:31,555
Forecasters are blaming the weather...

447
00:41:31,622 --> 00:41:35,326
on all the volcanoes, the earthquakes--

448
00:41:38,229 --> 00:41:40,564
There's all kinds of rumors.

449
00:41:44,335 --> 00:41:46,570
I'm a little scared.

450
00:41:48,973 --> 00:41:50,908
Jake ?

451
00:41:52,209 --> 00:41:54,678
Jake ?

452
00:41:54,745 --> 00:41:57,081
Jake ? Hello.

453
00:41:57,147 --> 00:41:59,149
Hello.

454
00:42:02,086 --> 00:42:06,357
No, sir. We didn't expect it in quadrant one for another week.

455
00:42:07,758 --> 00:42:10,461
Yes, sir. I'm preparing to take position...

456
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:13,631
at main control shortly. [ Electronic Beeping ]

457
00:42:13,697 --> 00:42:16,133
I will.

458
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:18,135
Are you outta here ?

459
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:20,137
Almost.

460
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:22,907
You gonna be okay by yourself ? Yes, sir.

461
00:42:22,973 --> 00:42:25,743
Keep me alerted on any changes. When that thing gets close,

462
00:42:25,809 --> 00:42:29,947
- start taking pictures, lots of pictures. - Roger that. Sir ?

463
00:42:30,014 --> 00:42:33,217
What are the chances of Last Dance not coming through ?

464
00:42:33,284 --> 00:42:36,921
I don't know. We hope for the best.

465
00:42:36,987 --> 00:42:40,324
We'll get used to the idea of spending the next 30 years underground.

466
00:42:53,137 --> 00:42:56,473
[ Woman Over P.A. ] Last Dance countdown on schedule.

467
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:58,742
Twenty-two minutes, mark.

468
00:43:25,402 --> 00:43:28,138
[ Alarm Blaring ]

469
00:43:33,377 --> 00:43:36,313
[ Alarm Continues ]

470
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:39,516
Hold it right there ! Stop, or I'll shoot !

471
00:43:48,592 --> 00:43:51,662
[ Alarm Continues ] What are you doing here ?

472
00:43:51,729 --> 00:43:54,498
I got the key.

473
00:43:54,565 --> 00:43:56,667
They can't launch. Who are you ?

474
00:43:56,734 --> 00:43:59,303
What key ? The key to the missile, genius.

475
00:44:02,206 --> 00:44:05,209
You stopped the missile ?

476
00:44:05,275 --> 00:44:07,711
Give me that !

477
00:44:12,416 --> 00:44:14,518
Aah !

478
00:44:16,587 --> 00:44:19,656
[ Groaning ]

479
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:22,893
I'm on your side. I'm on your side !

480
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:25,529
Hey ! Hey !

481
00:44:27,398 --> 00:44:29,767
Hey ! Stop him !

482
00:44:34,238 --> 00:44:38,308
Hey ! He's got the key ! Get him ! Do whatever it takes !

483
00:44:39,443 --> 00:44:41,378
[ Yells ]

484
00:44:41,445 --> 00:44:44,548
[ Woman Over P.A. ] T minus six minutes until launch window.

485
00:44:44,615 --> 00:44:47,117
Sir ? This was the last chance.

486
00:44:47,184 --> 00:44:49,787
After all these years of work, and now this.

487
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:52,256
I told you a month ago, we need more control.

488
00:44:52,322 --> 00:44:54,324
If we can't get that missile launched--

489
00:44:54,391 --> 00:44:56,927
This man must know that he's destroyed our future.

490
00:44:56,994 --> 00:45:00,297
- What would they want with the missile ? - It isn't one of the rebels.

491
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:02,966
Well, who is it, then ?

492
00:45:03,033 --> 00:45:05,602
Records show he's not one of ours.

493
00:45:05,669 --> 00:45:09,339
Barnet in Lower Operations reported a trespasser this morning.

494
00:45:12,676 --> 00:45:15,746
I don't care who he is. Get the key back.

495
00:45:15,813 --> 00:45:18,615
Done. [ Footsteps ]

496
00:45:18,682 --> 00:45:21,652
[ Pete ] Stan, what do you want ? Sorry, Doc.

497
00:45:21,718 --> 00:45:24,721
I think I can help. I know him.

498
00:45:26,690 --> 00:45:29,693
[ Woman Over P.A. ] T minus four minutes until launch window.

499
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:32,963
[ Alarm Continues ]

500
00:45:33,030 --> 00:45:36,300
Last Dance launch. All systems still go.

501
00:45:36,366 --> 00:45:39,269
[ Alarm Continues ]

502
00:45:41,905 --> 00:45:46,710
[ Man Over P.A. ] Mr. Jake Lowe, we know who you are.

503
00:45:46,777 --> 00:45:51,348
Surrender and return the key immediately, and no harm will come to you.

504
00:45:52,216 --> 00:45:54,451
Son of a bitch !

505
00:45:56,854 --> 00:46:00,724
[ Woman Over P.A. ] T minus three minutes and counting.

506
00:46:19,543 --> 00:46:22,546
Take him out. I don't care. Get the key.

507
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:26,183
We're trying, sir. We got him pinned down in corridor "C."

508
00:46:26,250 --> 00:46:29,186
No, you can't shoot him ! He's a good friend. I can talk to him.

509
00:46:29,253 --> 00:46:32,156
Stan, he's jeopardizing our entire operation.

510
00:46:37,728 --> 00:46:39,663
[ Clicking ]

511
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:45,736
Over here ! This way !

512
00:46:45,803 --> 00:46:49,406
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go !

513
00:46:51,808 --> 00:46:55,012
T minus two minutes and counting.

514
00:46:55,078 --> 00:46:57,414
[ Man ] Freeze ! Don't move !

515
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:02,886
- Come any closer, and I'll drop it ! - Be very careful !

516
00:47:02,953 --> 00:47:05,889
Screw you.

517
00:47:10,093 --> 00:47:13,564
Jake, no !

518
00:47:13,630 --> 00:47:16,233
- What the hell is this, Stan ? - You don't understand, Jake.

519
00:47:16,300 --> 00:47:19,269
Where's that missile headed ? How many people are gonna die for Last Dance ?

520
00:47:19,336 --> 00:47:22,439
No, look, you're on the wrong track, buddy.

521
00:47:22,506 --> 00:47:26,677
This time, they die if we don't launch. Now, please, give me the key.

522
00:47:28,178 --> 00:47:31,848
Tell 'em to drop their guns.

523
00:47:31,915 --> 00:47:35,552
- Put the guns down. Put 'em down ! - Put 'em down.

524
00:47:38,722 --> 00:47:42,359
You gotta trust me on this one. Come on, partner.

525
00:47:42,426 --> 00:47:46,496
I never let you down before, have I ? Give me the key, buddy.

526
00:47:47,731 --> 00:47:50,567
Please, Jake.

527
00:47:50,634 --> 00:47:54,338
T minus 45 seconds and counting.

528
00:47:56,940 --> 00:47:58,642
Good.

529
00:47:58,709 --> 00:48:00,911
Get this to control, now !

530
00:48:06,917 --> 00:48:09,920
T minus 20 seconds and counting.

531
00:48:18,562 --> 00:48:20,330
T minus ten seconds.

532
00:48:20,397 --> 00:48:23,967
Nine, eight,

533
00:48:24,034 --> 00:48:28,005
seven, six, five,

534
00:48:28,071 --> 00:48:31,808
four, three,

535
00:48:31,875 --> 00:48:34,645
two, one.

536
00:48:42,986 --> 00:48:45,355
[ Man Over P.A. ] Last Dance is away.

537
00:48:53,664 --> 00:48:57,501
[ Man Over P.A. ] Trajectory normal. All systems go.

538
00:48:57,567 --> 00:48:59,903
Hit it, you bastard.

539
00:48:59,970 --> 00:49:03,173
Did we make the launch window, sir ?

540
00:49:03,240 --> 00:49:05,609
Barely.

541
00:49:05,676 --> 00:49:07,911
Barely.

542
00:49:07,978 --> 00:49:10,747
How long until it reaches Tycus ?

543
00:49:10,814 --> 00:49:14,484
[ Sighs ] Nine and a half very sleepless hours.

544
00:49:18,722 --> 00:49:22,326
Relax the grip. He's not going anywhere.

545
00:49:25,729 --> 00:49:28,165
[ Feedback ] This is Dr. Crawford.

546
00:49:28,231 --> 00:49:31,668
Operation Last Dance has begun.

547
00:49:31,735 --> 00:49:36,306
Uh, there's nothing more that we can do for the time being except hope.

548
00:49:36,373 --> 00:49:40,377
[ Sighs ] Try to get some rest, everyone. Thank you.

549
00:49:40,444 --> 00:49:42,412
[ Button Clicks ]

550
00:49:42,479 --> 00:49:44,581
Sir.

551
00:49:44,648 --> 00:49:47,884
What do you wanna do about him ?

552
00:49:49,286 --> 00:49:51,588
How did you get in here ?

553
00:49:51,655 --> 00:49:54,358
Nobody locked the screen door.

554
00:49:54,424 --> 00:49:59,062
I'm too tired to try to explain to you what you almost stopped.

555
00:49:59,129 --> 00:50:01,732
[ Sighs ] Get rid of him.

556
00:50:01,798 --> 00:50:05,235
Dr. Crawford, please. Let me spend some time with him.

557
00:50:08,638 --> 00:50:10,674
All right.

558
00:50:21,685 --> 00:50:24,588
[ Beeping ]

559
00:50:40,303 --> 00:50:43,373
How you been, soldier ?

560
00:50:45,542 --> 00:50:48,078
Why don't we catch up on the last five years another time,

561
00:50:48,145 --> 00:50:52,783
and you tell me why you brought me here and what the hell is going on ?

562
00:50:52,849 --> 00:50:56,620
There's a comet, Jake-- or rather, a piece of one.

563
00:50:57,821 --> 00:51:00,490
Crawford's calling it Tycus. Tycus.

564
00:51:00,557 --> 00:51:02,959
And now it's on its way here.

565
00:51:04,294 --> 00:51:07,497
- Is it gonna hit ? - Not us, the moon.

566
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:11,735
It'll destroy it.

567
00:51:11,802 --> 00:51:15,572
And the gravitational pull against the earth will be enormous.

568
00:51:15,639 --> 00:51:20,010
We're talking tidal waves, Jake, earthquakes, fires, floods.

569
00:51:20,077 --> 00:51:22,979
If this is all true, how come no one else knows ?

570
00:51:23,046 --> 00:51:26,149
It was ten years ago when the comet was discovered.

571
00:51:26,216 --> 00:51:29,820
Crawford's calculations were published in scientific journals.

572
00:51:29,886 --> 00:51:31,955
No one took him seriously.

573
00:51:32,022 --> 00:51:34,791
Just another harmless light show.

574
00:51:34,858 --> 00:51:38,628
So Crawford didn't want to wait, so he built this.

575
00:51:38,695 --> 00:51:41,131
A nuclear missile site.

576
00:51:41,198 --> 00:51:43,300
The missile's only a last chance.

577
00:51:43,366 --> 00:51:46,002
Operation Archangel's the backup plan,

578
00:51:46,069 --> 00:51:50,607
built by the best from their respective fields with two focuses:

579
00:51:50,674 --> 00:51:53,510
One, to deter the comet,

580
00:51:53,577 --> 00:51:56,847
or, if worst comes to worst, provide a safe haven,

581
00:51:56,913 --> 00:52:00,383
a modern-day Noah's Ark to save humanity here on Earth.

582
00:52:00,450 --> 00:52:03,753
How the hell did you get involved in this ?

583
00:52:03,820 --> 00:52:06,623
I was just what they were looking for--

584
00:52:06,690 --> 00:52:09,626
a writer, a photographer, someone who could document the project.

585
00:52:09,693 --> 00:52:11,728
The more I learned,

586
00:52:11,795 --> 00:52:15,465
the more I spoke to Crawford, the more I came to realize that he was right--

587
00:52:15,532 --> 00:52:17,801
that there needs to be this place,

588
00:52:17,868 --> 00:52:21,371
that we're going to be the fathers of a new age.

589
00:52:21,438 --> 00:52:25,242
You're both fucking crazy. I wish I was, Jake.

590
00:52:25,308 --> 00:52:27,410
Tycus is coming.

591
00:52:27,477 --> 00:52:30,480
I'm as sure of it as I've ever been about anything in my life.

592
00:52:33,984 --> 00:52:36,920
This place must've cost millions to build.

593
00:52:36,987 --> 00:52:39,689
[ Stan ] The money flowed in like water.

594
00:52:39,756 --> 00:52:43,326
But Crawford was smart. No celebrities, no politicians.

595
00:52:43,393 --> 00:52:45,495
Only rich, powerful people,

596
00:52:45,562 --> 00:52:50,166
people who would pay millions for a small spot and keep quiet about it.

597
00:52:52,235 --> 00:52:55,772
If you're right, you can't keep it a secret.

598
00:52:55,839 --> 00:52:59,342
There's only so much space. There's only one chance.

599
00:52:59,409 --> 00:53:02,679
And that's why I thought I should let you in on it.

600
00:53:05,282 --> 00:53:08,952
I got a wife... and a baby.

601
00:53:11,588 --> 00:53:14,024
I didn't know you got married.

602
00:53:15,926 --> 00:53:18,461
There's only so many spaces.

603
00:53:18,528 --> 00:53:21,898
I'm sorry. Oh, you're sorry.

604
00:53:33,677 --> 00:53:36,546
Why don't you, uh,

605
00:53:36,613 --> 00:53:38,715
get some sleep, huh ?

606
00:53:41,218 --> 00:53:45,455
Look, I'll do everything I can to keep you safe.

607
00:53:47,791 --> 00:53:49,726
[ Beeping ]

608
00:54:11,615 --> 00:54:13,583
Let's go.

609
00:54:13,650 --> 00:54:15,285
[ Shutter Clicking ]

610
00:54:15,352 --> 00:54:18,054
Tycus is 3.9 million miles.

611
00:54:18,121 --> 00:54:20,890
Last Dance closing. Radius: 4-2-5.

612
00:54:20,957 --> 00:54:22,892
All systems still go.

613
00:54:30,200 --> 00:54:32,636
[ Camera Shutter Clicking ] Fifth thruster is a go.

614
00:54:32,702 --> 00:54:34,771
Preparing sixth and final thruster.

615
00:54:34,838 --> 00:54:37,207
Last Dance vector is good.

616
00:54:37,273 --> 00:54:40,543
[ Beeping ]

617
00:54:40,610 --> 00:54:44,381
Right on target. This is it.

618
00:54:50,453 --> 00:54:54,491
If I didn't know you better, I'd swear you were hoping for a miss.

619
00:54:54,557 --> 00:54:57,727
Give you a chance to record the new age.

620
00:54:57,794 --> 00:54:59,729
All systems still go.

621
00:55:03,933 --> 00:55:07,837
[ Woman Over P.A. ] T minus 20 seconds until detonation.

622
00:55:07,904 --> 00:55:09,973
19,

623
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:12,742
18, 17,

624
00:55:13,877 --> 00:55:17,113
16, 15,

625
00:55:17,180 --> 00:55:20,550
14, 13,

626
00:55:20,617 --> 00:55:23,053
12, 11.

627
00:55:23,119 --> 00:55:25,855
T minus ten seconds.

628
00:55:25,922 --> 00:55:29,659
Nine, eight,

629
00:55:29,726 --> 00:55:32,662
seven, six,

630
00:55:32,729 --> 00:55:35,932
five, four,

631
00:55:35,999 --> 00:55:37,667
three,

632
00:55:37,734 --> 00:55:40,136
two, one.

633
00:55:40,203 --> 00:55:42,138
Detonate.

634
00:55:54,951 --> 00:55:56,920
Negative.

635
00:55:56,986 --> 00:56:00,090
Last Dance detonated at correct window of opportunity,

636
00:56:00,156 --> 00:56:03,093
but Tycus remains on course.

637
00:56:03,159 --> 00:56:07,430
It's like it never even blinked, sir.

638
00:56:07,497 --> 00:56:09,933
Tycus is now approaching Earth's atmosphere.

639
00:56:09,999 --> 00:56:12,769
Estimated time of collision with the moon:

640
00:56:12,836 --> 00:56:16,272
nine hours, 32 minutes and ten seconds.

641
00:56:19,342 --> 00:56:22,212
[ Button Clicks ] Crawford here.

642
00:56:22,278 --> 00:56:25,148
Well, remember, we prepared for this,

643
00:56:25,215 --> 00:56:27,417
and, uh, we press on...

644
00:56:27,484 --> 00:56:31,387
with Operation Archangel.

645
00:56:31,454 --> 00:56:34,224
Everything is all right.

646
00:56:34,290 --> 00:56:36,392
[ Button Clicks ] Menkees.

647
00:56:38,461 --> 00:56:41,231
I want you to send for Helen and Jamie.

648
00:56:41,297 --> 00:56:44,134
I want 'em here as soon as possible. It's done.

649
00:56:44,200 --> 00:56:46,236
Thank you. I want him outta here !

650
00:56:46,302 --> 00:56:48,571
- Menkees, no ! - I gotta get to Amy !

651
00:56:48,638 --> 00:56:51,241
Right now. Let's go. Wait ! Menkees.

652
00:56:53,710 --> 00:56:57,747
Six years. Six years, you've known about this ! Take him up to the surface.

653
00:56:57,814 --> 00:57:01,818
Let him free. Free to die. But you can't do that.

654
00:57:01,885 --> 00:57:04,487
- He can be valuable to us. - There's no room. You know the policy.

655
00:57:04,554 --> 00:57:06,489
That policy-- That policy's the law !

656
00:57:06,556 --> 00:57:08,992
[ Groans ] Only one we got left.

657
00:57:09,058 --> 00:57:11,427
Thanks for being such a pain in the ass.

658
00:57:11,494 --> 00:57:14,364
I'm not done yet. Yeah, you are.

659
00:57:14,430 --> 00:57:16,666
[ Jake ] You're gonna burn in hell, Crawford.

660
00:57:16,733 --> 00:57:18,835
No, son, the earth is.

661
00:57:18,902 --> 00:57:21,171
No, get him outta there. No, it's all right.

662
00:57:21,237 --> 00:57:24,441
He's only going a few floors higher. Dr. Crawford, hear me out.

663
00:57:24,507 --> 00:57:27,777
You let me in. Trust my judgment now.

664
00:57:27,844 --> 00:57:31,781
I'm sorry, Stan, but you should just feel lucky enough as it is.

665
00:57:31,848 --> 00:57:33,783
Wait !

666
00:57:40,757 --> 00:57:45,361
How can you sleep at night, knowing all those women and children will be lost ?

667
00:57:46,529 --> 00:57:48,231
I didn't send Tycus.

668
00:57:48,298 --> 00:57:52,302
You witnessed me try to destroy it. I can't save every life.

669
00:57:52,368 --> 00:57:55,405
Just the ones you choose. Oh, no, look.

670
00:57:55,471 --> 00:58:00,343
Once the people of this planet discovered their fate, do you think all wars would stop ?

671
00:58:00,410 --> 00:58:03,580
Do you think neighbors would embrace neighbors ?

672
00:58:03,646 --> 00:58:07,550
Maybe. But at least I'd have given them the chance.

673
00:58:08,618 --> 00:58:11,588
Well, you're a dreaming fool.

674
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:14,591
It would have been total chaos.

675
00:58:14,657 --> 00:58:17,293
[ Computerized Voice ] Level six. Access restricted.

676
00:58:17,360 --> 00:58:20,230
I wish you the best of luck.

677
00:58:20,296 --> 00:58:22,665
I can't let you stay.

678
00:58:33,776 --> 00:58:37,146
[ Computerized Voice ] Surface level. Please stand clear.

679
00:58:37,213 --> 00:58:40,016
[ Grunts ]

680
00:58:40,083 --> 00:58:43,553
Jake, what are you doing ? No, Jake, stop it !

681
00:58:59,202 --> 00:59:01,838
[ Grunts ]

682
00:59:10,747 --> 00:59:13,082
[ Groaning ]

683
00:59:13,149 --> 00:59:15,585
Now there's one more spot.

684
00:59:15,652 --> 00:59:18,655
[ Continues Groaning ]

685
00:59:22,825 --> 00:59:25,094
[ Groans ]

686
00:59:28,865 --> 00:59:30,800
He's got a name, Jake.

687
00:59:30,867 --> 00:59:34,137
It's William. He's a friend.

688
00:59:34,203 --> 00:59:37,140
The decision's a lot harder than you think.

689
00:59:48,851 --> 00:59:52,221
- [ Stan ] Look. - [ Groans ]

690
00:59:52,288 --> 00:59:57,327
I can keep you in my dorm until Tycus passes. Then they can't throw you out.

691
00:59:57,393 --> 01:00:00,897
I'm gonna get my wife and baby, Stan.

692
01:00:00,964 --> 01:00:03,499
Hit Crawford's floor.

693
01:00:03,566 --> 01:00:06,903
It's security coded. The guard's the only one who'll know it.

694
01:00:09,672 --> 01:00:12,942
- Hit Crawford's floor. - Fuck you.

695
01:00:14,010 --> 01:00:15,945
No, Jake !

696
01:00:16,012 --> 01:00:18,982
- Jake ! - Pretty please.

697
01:00:19,048 --> 01:00:20,984
Jake, no !

698
01:00:23,619 --> 01:00:26,823
[ Beeping ]

699
01:00:26,889 --> 01:00:30,727
[ Computerized Voice ] Level six. Access restricted.

700
01:00:55,785 --> 01:01:00,089
[ Woman ] At a press conference earlier today at J.P.L., a spokesman confirmed...

701
01:01:00,156 --> 01:01:04,160
that the comet will pass close to the Earth's orbital territory.

702
01:01:04,227 --> 01:01:06,896
Members of the scientific community point out that a comet...

703
01:01:06,963 --> 01:01:11,267
does not need to actually hit the Earth to cause considerable damage.

704
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:15,004
In a related story, Washington will not deny or confirm...

705
01:01:15,071 --> 01:01:18,541
reports of a small missile launch early this morning.

706
01:01:20,376 --> 01:01:22,412
Um, I've just received this update.

707
01:01:23,880 --> 01:01:26,749
Sources have reported rumors that an underground shelter...

708
01:01:26,816 --> 01:01:30,987
large enough to house the population of a small town may exist.

709
01:01:31,054 --> 01:01:34,190
An exact location is unknown at this time.

710
01:01:52,508 --> 01:01:54,944
They know ! They know !

711
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:58,748
Archangel is now public knowledge.

712
01:01:58,815 --> 01:02:00,917
Repeat: Archangel is known to the public.

713
01:02:00,983 --> 01:02:03,086
Consider this a security alert.

714
01:02:03,152 --> 01:02:06,222
All personnel underground cease all surface action.

715
01:02:06,289 --> 01:02:08,791
Operation Full Knowledge is now in effect.

716
01:02:08,858 --> 01:02:11,160
Well, this is it, my friends.

717
01:02:11,227 --> 01:02:13,696
The new age has begun.

718
01:02:15,331 --> 01:02:19,235
[ Man Shouting ]

719
01:02:19,302 --> 01:02:22,205
Let's go ! Come on, you guys !

720
01:02:22,271 --> 01:02:24,841
Kelly, go to section "B." "B" !

721
01:02:29,479 --> 01:02:32,115
Lock it up ! Lock it up !

722
01:02:35,952 --> 01:02:40,623
[ Man Over Loudspeaker ] All personnel report to their designated areas immediately.

723
01:02:41,724 --> 01:02:44,427
Commence lockdown sequence.

724
01:02:44,494 --> 01:02:48,131
Operation Full Knowledge initiated.

725
01:02:48,197 --> 01:02:51,968
Operation Full Knowledge initiated.

726
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:06,182
This is it. It's our last chance.

727
01:03:07,850 --> 01:03:10,319
I'm gonna go to Crawford's floor via the east wing. You take the west.

728
01:03:10,386 --> 01:03:13,523
Whoever sees him first, take him.

729
01:03:13,589 --> 01:03:15,525
Let's go. Right.

730
01:03:15,591 --> 01:03:18,961
Sir, you can't come through here.

731
01:03:26,903 --> 01:03:29,238
Security enforcement now in effect.

732
01:03:29,305 --> 01:03:33,176
Proper identification must be presented upon request.

733
01:03:44,954 --> 01:03:47,390
[ Phone Ringing ]

734
01:03:56,866 --> 01:03:58,868
Hello.

735
01:03:58,935 --> 01:04:00,870
Yeah, Anderson ? It's Crawford here.

736
01:04:02,438 --> 01:04:06,542
What ? No one was sent for Helen and Jamie ?

737
01:04:06,609 --> 01:04:10,680
But I distinctly told Menkees I--

738
01:04:10,746 --> 01:04:12,982
Try to call them. Get them on the phone.

739
01:04:13,049 --> 01:04:15,318
W-We've got to get 'em before it's too late. Hurry !

740
01:04:23,292 --> 01:04:26,095
- Menkees, what are you doing ? - There's no cause for alarm.

741
01:04:26,162 --> 01:04:30,099
We just have a little business to take care of, and we don't have much time to do it.

742
01:04:30,166 --> 01:04:33,803
Menkees, of all the people. Why you ?

743
01:04:35,171 --> 01:04:38,040
Loved ones, Pete. Loved ones.

744
01:04:38,107 --> 01:04:42,111
But you were given two slots just like the rest of us. I mean, you have your wife here,

745
01:04:42,178 --> 01:04:44,580
your eldest son-- What more could you want ?

746
01:04:44,647 --> 01:04:48,584
My other child, for starters.

747
01:04:48,651 --> 01:04:52,054
Look, it might not be fair, but I'm not gonna live without any of them.

748
01:04:53,823 --> 01:04:57,326
Now, I want one of those jets fueled and waiting,

749
01:04:57,393 --> 01:05:00,663
and I want the code to get back in from you.

750
01:05:00,730 --> 01:05:04,834
That's all. I'm not being unrealistic. Four more.

751
01:05:04,900 --> 01:05:09,038
This is a zero sum game here, Menkees.

752
01:05:09,105 --> 01:05:13,509
One person comes in, that's another one of us who dies.

753
01:05:13,576 --> 01:05:16,045
Well, I already took care of that. As it happens,

754
01:05:16,112 --> 01:05:18,748
on my way up here, four new spots opened up.

755
01:05:20,216 --> 01:05:23,119
Oh, my God.

756
01:05:23,185 --> 01:05:25,821
Please put the gun down and be reasonable.

757
01:05:25,888 --> 01:05:30,926
We've all known from the beginning that this is the way it had to be.

758
01:05:33,229 --> 01:05:36,932
I want the code, Peter. Now.

759
01:05:36,999 --> 01:05:42,405
[ Crawford ] If I give you the code, we'll all die here.

760
01:05:42,471 --> 01:05:47,343
Do you have any idea how many people will follow you back and demand to get in here ?

761
01:05:51,947 --> 01:05:55,051
Now, I want that code.

762
01:05:56,118 --> 01:05:58,688
There are others with you, Menkees.

763
01:05:58,754 --> 01:06:03,793
Munson. He was one of yours, wasn't he ?

764
01:06:08,097 --> 01:06:10,466
Now, I don't have time for questions.

765
01:06:10,533 --> 01:06:15,237
And I'm not gonna ask again. Go to hell.

766
01:06:16,639 --> 01:06:18,674
[ Gunshot ]

767
01:06:25,314 --> 01:06:27,383
[ Screams ]

768
01:06:41,163 --> 01:06:43,766
It's okay. I'm all right now.

769
01:06:45,234 --> 01:06:48,170
Put the guns down.

770
01:06:48,237 --> 01:06:51,374
Put 'em down !

771
01:06:51,440 --> 01:06:54,276
You have my thanks and you're welcome to stay here.

772
01:06:54,343 --> 01:06:57,246
Fire up the jet. I'm going to Los Angeles.

773
01:06:57,313 --> 01:07:01,117
- You're leaving ? - It's my family.

774
01:07:01,183 --> 01:07:03,586
I wanted them to have every last minute of a normal life.

775
01:07:03,652 --> 01:07:06,255
I couldn't bring myself to locking them up in here...

776
01:07:06,322 --> 01:07:08,457
any sooner than I had to.

777
01:07:08,524 --> 01:07:10,459
Well, then you'll understand why I'm doing this.

778
01:07:12,027 --> 01:07:14,964
Out of the way. Boss man's coming with me.

779
01:07:15,030 --> 01:07:18,968
- [ Crawford ] You don't have to do that. - I got a wife...

780
01:07:19,034 --> 01:07:20,970
and a kid comin'.

781
01:07:21,036 --> 01:07:25,508
Well, then come with me. But put the gun away, for crying out loud.

782
01:07:26,575 --> 01:07:28,511
Why should I believe you ?

783
01:07:28,577 --> 01:07:32,148
Because you saved my life and I owe you, and I'm a man of my word.

784
01:07:32,214 --> 01:07:34,650
And I know what you're feeling right now.

785
01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:37,953
Put that down ! It's all right.

786
01:07:42,625 --> 01:07:44,760
Put it down ! It's all right !

787
01:07:47,863 --> 01:07:50,166
It's okay. Come on, let's go.

788
01:07:53,469 --> 01:07:56,505
[ Computerized Female Voice ] Tycus' E.T.A.:

789
01:07:56,572 --> 01:07:58,874
five hours, 40 minutes.

790
01:07:58,941 --> 01:08:01,377
Trajectory: constant.

791
01:08:05,581 --> 01:08:08,083
[ Beeping ]

792
01:08:10,386 --> 01:08:12,655
Hey, what are you doing here ? Get outta here. Sorry, Doc,

793
01:08:12,721 --> 01:08:15,157
but I owe this man.

794
01:08:15,224 --> 01:08:17,660
I got him into this.

795
01:08:19,094 --> 01:08:22,832
I'm gonna help get him out.

796
01:08:24,433 --> 01:08:27,736
[ Computerized Voice ] Surface level. Please stand clear.

797
01:08:27,803 --> 01:08:31,040
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

798
01:08:31,107 --> 01:08:33,542
[ Thunderclap ]

799
01:08:39,348 --> 01:08:44,019
Stan, your work is far too important to be coming with us.

800
01:08:44,086 --> 01:08:47,723
What I see up here will be as big a piece of history as what I see down there. Bigger.

801
01:08:47,790 --> 01:08:50,793
Besides, you're gonna need me.

802
01:08:52,428 --> 01:08:54,864
[ Woman ] The comet that earlier was thought to be harmless...

803
01:08:54,930 --> 01:08:58,234
is now on a collision course with the moon.

804
01:08:58,300 --> 01:09:02,638
There is a distinct possibility that the fragments could come crashing to Earth...

805
01:09:02,705 --> 01:09:05,341
and cause serious damage. Got those proofs for you, boss.

806
01:09:05,407 --> 01:09:08,177
Specialists from NASA and J.P.L. in Pasadena...

807
01:09:08,244 --> 01:09:13,916
are advising all emergency and governmental agencies to have evacuation plans in place...

808
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:17,987
for some urban and low-lying areas in the United States.

809
01:09:18,053 --> 01:09:21,223
Right now, coastal communities and large cities...

810
01:09:21,290 --> 01:09:23,926
are at the greatest risk.

811
01:09:23,993 --> 01:09:26,729
There's no need to panic.

812
01:09:26,795 --> 01:09:31,300
Please stay tuned to this station for more late-breaking news and information.

813
01:09:32,535 --> 01:09:36,739
Still want to run that miracle diet pill story ?

814
01:09:47,416 --> 01:09:51,320
Come on, baby, pick it up. Pick it up.

815
01:09:51,387 --> 01:09:53,589
You know, the phone lines are probably down.

816
01:09:53,656 --> 01:09:55,591
[ Line Ringing ]

817
01:09:58,160 --> 01:10:00,963
What happened with Menkees ?

818
01:10:01,030 --> 01:10:03,332
[ Sighs ]

819
01:10:03,399 --> 01:10:06,468
Everyone was to bring two immediate family members.

820
01:10:06,535 --> 01:10:09,205
That was the deal. That was the best I could do.

821
01:10:09,271 --> 01:10:11,373
Menkees was no exception.

822
01:10:11,440 --> 01:10:14,510
He got greedy.

823
01:10:16,111 --> 01:10:18,981
Who gave you the right to decide who lives and who dies ?

824
01:10:19,048 --> 01:10:22,451
Try to understand this. I was the first to see the comet.

825
01:10:22,518 --> 01:10:26,855
I presented my findings to the scientific community.

826
01:10:26,922 --> 01:10:29,658
They chose to ignore me. I am just as upset...

827
01:10:29,725 --> 01:10:34,330
about those who are going to be left behind as anyone, please believe me.

828
01:10:34,396 --> 01:10:37,166
- Bullshit ! - What is bullshit ?

829
01:10:38,701 --> 01:10:42,504
- You're playing God. - I am not playing God.

830
01:10:42,571 --> 01:10:47,142
We are living in His miracle. I am trying to save it.

831
01:10:47,209 --> 01:10:51,480
Jake, look, there is no happy ending to either side of the argument.

832
01:10:51,547 --> 01:10:54,617
One side has to be sacrificed so that the other can survive.

833
01:10:54,683 --> 01:10:57,186
We're not talking about equations, we're talking about people.

834
01:10:57,253 --> 01:11:00,656
And whose job is it to make that choice ? Yours ?

835
01:11:00,723 --> 01:11:03,192
Well, maybe we should choose not to save anyone.

836
01:11:06,161 --> 01:11:08,664
Do you wanna live or do you wanna die ?

837
01:11:08,731 --> 01:11:11,634
- You didn't give that choice to Munson. - No, but I'm giving it to you.

838
01:11:11,700 --> 01:11:15,170
You saved my life. I'm offering to save yours.

839
01:11:15,237 --> 01:11:20,376
- Well, thanks for including me. - You are now part of the continuum of humanity.

840
01:11:21,443 --> 01:11:23,712
Act accordingly.

841
01:11:42,498 --> 01:11:45,034
[ Sighs ]

842
01:11:46,769 --> 01:11:51,674
- He's somethin', isn't he ? - Oh, he's out of this world, partner.

843
01:11:51,740 --> 01:11:55,244
- So are you. - You're not getting it, Jake.

844
01:11:55,311 --> 01:11:57,413
Crawford had the same questions you're having.

845
01:11:57,479 --> 01:12:01,850
But he fought the battle. He made a decision. You haven't.

846
01:12:01,917 --> 01:12:04,186
You're right.

847
01:12:04,253 --> 01:12:06,989
I didn't create an entire underworld and place myself in a position...

848
01:12:07,056 --> 01:12:09,658
to dictate the destiny of the human race.

849
01:12:09,725 --> 01:12:12,428
Is that what's bothering you, that you didn't come up with the answer ?

850
01:12:13,829 --> 01:12:16,098
Why can't you cross the line, Jake ?

851
01:12:16,165 --> 01:12:19,868
Because it's there. That line has always been there, Stan.

852
01:12:21,203 --> 01:12:24,206
What if he's wrong ?

853
01:12:24,273 --> 01:12:29,411
There's a plan, and maybe that plan is that this is the end.

854
01:12:29,478 --> 01:12:33,382
Or maybe it's a test to see if we can do the right thing, I don't know.

855
01:12:35,784 --> 01:12:38,187
I just keep thinkin' that--

856
01:12:38,253 --> 01:12:42,958
- Everything we need has been placed here for us. - That's right.

857
01:12:43,025 --> 01:12:47,463
And Peter Crawford took what was given to him and created Archangel.

858
01:12:48,530 --> 01:12:50,733
Now, what's wrong with that ?

859
01:12:53,836 --> 01:12:56,638
Think about it.

860
01:13:11,954 --> 01:13:14,056
[ Bell Dings ]

861
01:13:20,629 --> 01:13:23,365
Gary, what's the problem ? Oh.

862
01:13:23,432 --> 01:13:26,235
No air traffic control at L.A.X.

863
01:13:26,301 --> 01:13:29,738
There's accidents on two separate runways; 15 planes are circling;

864
01:13:29,805 --> 01:13:32,341
Santa Monica is inundated with big jets they can't handle.

865
01:13:32,407 --> 01:13:36,478
All right. I know a place just above L.A.

866
01:13:36,545 --> 01:13:38,947
It's a small airstrip. I think I can remember where it is.

867
01:13:39,014 --> 01:13:40,949
[ Crawford ] I hope to hell you got a good memory.

868
01:13:41,016 --> 01:13:43,419
[ Woman ] All major freeways are currently jammed.

869
01:13:43,485 --> 01:13:46,355
When possible, use alternate routes.

870
01:13:46,422 --> 01:13:48,924
The National Guard will be monitoring the highways...

871
01:13:48,991 --> 01:13:53,962
along with regional authorities to maintain order and provide assistance where needed.

872
01:13:54,029 --> 01:13:55,998
Bob ? Thank you, Kelly.

873
01:13:56,064 --> 01:13:58,233
[ Bob ] Once again, here is that evacuation number:

874
01:13:58,300 --> 01:14:02,571
1-888-752-3559.

875
01:14:02,638 --> 01:14:06,308
Call this for the location of the nearest center in your area.

876
01:14:06,375 --> 01:14:08,610
Families in the metro and coastal areas are being urged to report...

877
01:14:08,677 --> 01:14:12,447
to their nearest evacuation center for information...

878
01:14:12,514 --> 01:14:15,417
or head east into the desert communities.

879
01:14:15,484 --> 01:14:17,920
And now, let's go live to David Jones standing by...

880
01:14:17,986 --> 01:14:20,823
at the emergency center in Palmdale. David ?

881
01:14:25,360 --> 01:14:28,697
1800 hours, that's when the real shit's gonna hit the fan.

882
01:14:28,764 --> 01:14:31,900
That gives us an hour search time,

883
01:14:31,967 --> 01:14:34,436
uh, two hours fly back,

884
01:14:34,503 --> 01:14:36,505
thirty minutes wiggle time if anything goes wrong.

885
01:14:36,572 --> 01:14:39,474
It won't. Well, let's hope not. We're not back...

886
01:14:39,541 --> 01:14:42,811
in an hour in a half, you take off without us.

887
01:14:42,878 --> 01:14:46,248
You save yourself. You don't worry about me.

888
01:14:46,315 --> 01:14:50,686
Don't leave the plane and don't open the door for anyone.

889
01:14:58,560 --> 01:15:02,097
[ Plane Approaching ]

890
01:15:02,164 --> 01:15:04,333
[ Tires Screeching ]

891
01:15:08,036 --> 01:15:11,173
H-Hey ! I thought I might see you again.

892
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:13,909
We havin' our drink now ? I gotta take a rain check.

893
01:15:13,976 --> 01:15:15,911
Can I borrow the truck just for about an hour ?

894
01:15:16,979 --> 01:15:18,914
We need to split up.

895
01:15:18,981 --> 01:15:21,650
Stan, I need you to keep an eye on the plane.

896
01:15:21,717 --> 01:15:23,886
I wrote down the code. Guard it with your life.

897
01:15:23,952 --> 01:15:26,588
If we're not back in time, you know what to do.

898
01:15:26,655 --> 01:15:28,590
Here, take the Caddy. It's fast.

899
01:15:30,692 --> 01:15:33,061
[ Engine Starts ] No hurry.

900
01:15:33,128 --> 01:15:35,797
You know, the world's gonna end !

901
01:15:37,532 --> 01:15:39,468
Jake !

902
01:15:41,303 --> 01:15:45,274
Hey, good luck.

903
01:15:45,340 --> 01:15:48,277
[ Engine Starts ]

904
01:15:51,980 --> 01:15:53,949
You ain't gonna like what you find out there.

905
01:16:04,293 --> 01:16:08,130
[ Man ] Broadcasters in your area cooperating with regional authorities...

906
01:16:08,196 --> 01:16:10,899
have set up this station in the event of an emergency.

907
01:16:10,966 --> 01:16:12,968
[ Alarm Sounding ] Stand by for instructions.

908
01:16:13,035 --> 01:16:15,604
In a moment you will be given important information--

909
01:16:15,671 --> 01:16:18,507
[ Signal Cuts Out ] Los Angeles area.

910
01:16:18,574 --> 01:16:21,009
Stand by for instructions.

911
01:16:24,813 --> 01:16:28,483
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

912
01:16:28,550 --> 01:16:32,020
I'm sorry. Where's your mother ?

913
01:16:32,087 --> 01:16:35,223
Oh, my God ! Put her down, you son of a bitch !

914
01:16:35,290 --> 01:16:37,292
Please, please. That's my baby ! Leave us alone !

915
01:16:37,359 --> 01:16:40,462
I'm just trying to help.

916
01:16:40,529 --> 01:16:43,465
Freeze, pal. Whoa.

917
01:16:43,532 --> 01:16:46,935
Don't shoot me, man.

918
01:16:47,002 --> 01:16:48,937
Thanks for the truck.

919
01:16:49,004 --> 01:16:51,306
Come on.

920
01:16:58,180 --> 01:17:01,216
[ Engine Starts ]

921
01:17:26,975 --> 01:17:32,547
[ All ] Our Father, Who art in heaven, hallowed be Thy name.

922
01:17:32,614 --> 01:17:35,017
Thy kingdom come, Thy will be done--

923
01:17:35,083 --> 01:17:37,753
[ Continues, Indistinct ] [ Whooping, Cheering ]

924
01:17:58,940 --> 01:18:01,176
Sources say that the underground dwelling...

925
01:18:01,243 --> 01:18:05,213
is located somewhere in the California Sierra mountain range.

926
01:18:05,280 --> 01:18:08,316
We now have a picture of the man most believe is responsible...

927
01:18:08,383 --> 01:18:11,653
for the underground safe haven refuge.

928
01:18:11,720 --> 01:18:15,957
His name is Dr. Peter Crawford, a physicist from Denver.

929
01:18:21,963 --> 01:18:23,532
[ Door Closes ] Amy ? [ Gasps ]

930
01:18:29,638 --> 01:18:32,007
[ Sobbing ]

931
01:18:32,074 --> 01:18:34,209
Oh, God. Are you okay ?

932
01:18:34,276 --> 01:18:36,878
I've been going crazy.

933
01:18:39,081 --> 01:18:41,316
Ohh.

934
01:18:41,383 --> 01:18:43,785
Sam came. He wanted me to go with him,

935
01:18:43,852 --> 01:18:45,954
but I wouldn't leave without you.

936
01:18:46,021 --> 01:18:48,490
There's no time. Come on.

937
01:19:09,878 --> 01:19:11,847
Peter.

938
01:19:12,914 --> 01:19:15,617
We're too late. What is it ?

939
01:19:15,684 --> 01:19:18,587
[ Helen ] What's going on ?

940
01:19:18,653 --> 01:19:21,089
The plane left.

941
01:19:22,190 --> 01:19:24,126
[ Helen ] Oh, my God.

942
01:19:26,027 --> 01:19:28,763
- Help here ! - Wait.

943
01:19:34,236 --> 01:19:38,140
[ Wheezing ] I tried to stop him.

944
01:19:38,206 --> 01:19:41,009
The pilot was just following orders.

945
01:19:41,076 --> 01:19:43,712
I'm sorry, Stan. I--

946
01:19:43,779 --> 01:19:45,947
I didn't want to leave without you and the Doc.

947
01:19:49,818 --> 01:19:52,487
Finish my book. Promise.

948
01:19:55,257 --> 01:19:57,659
Okay. [ Labored Breathing ]

949
01:20:03,365 --> 01:20:06,001
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

950
01:20:13,542 --> 01:20:16,378
Well, you heard him.

951
01:20:16,444 --> 01:20:18,980
It's up to you now.

952
01:20:20,715 --> 01:20:23,485
This feels wrong.

953
01:20:23,552 --> 01:20:26,321
All these people are gonna die, and I'm thinking about saving my family.

954
01:20:26,388 --> 01:20:30,025
That feeling never changes, son.

955
01:20:33,161 --> 01:20:36,198
Commander, can you give us a lift ?

956
01:20:59,187 --> 01:21:01,523
[ Instruments Beeping ]

957
01:21:05,760 --> 01:21:07,696
Oops.

958
01:21:07,762 --> 01:21:11,299
- What do you mean, "oops" ? - Nothin'.

959
01:21:11,366 --> 01:21:15,103
- You said "oops." What's the matter ? - Ah, we might have--

960
01:21:15,170 --> 01:21:17,939
- Might have busted an oil line. - Well, did you ?

961
01:21:23,378 --> 01:21:26,081
Yep. Definitely busted an oil line.

962
01:21:26,147 --> 01:21:28,650
- Shit. - Don't worry, though. Hey.

963
01:21:28,717 --> 01:21:31,720
We still got another problem. Uh, brace yourself.

964
01:21:31,786 --> 01:21:34,723
We gotta put her down. Do me a favor.

965
01:21:34,789 --> 01:21:38,059
Lower the landing gear there, chief. We're goin' in.

966
01:21:42,464 --> 01:21:45,567
[ Engine Knocking ] You bitch ! You bitch !

967
01:21:45,634 --> 01:21:47,969
- You don't want to cooperate today, do ya ? - What now ?

968
01:21:48,036 --> 01:21:50,772
No wheels. Don't worry, though. Don't worry.

969
01:21:50,839 --> 01:21:53,541
I can belly flop this thing right on a duck's dick.

970
01:21:53,608 --> 01:21:57,913
All right, folks, listen up in the back Better buckle up and hold on.

971
01:21:57,979 --> 01:22:03,184
And while you're at it, pray old Betsy here still has some heart left in her.

972
01:22:03,251 --> 01:22:08,123
We're goin' in ! [ Chuckles ] Man, it feels good to say that again.

973
01:22:08,189 --> 01:22:10,525
We're goin' in !

974
01:22:20,168 --> 01:22:22,604
Come on, baby.

975
01:22:22,671 --> 01:22:25,440
Come on, baby.

976
01:22:28,777 --> 01:22:32,113
Don't fall apart on me. Come on, baby.

977
01:22:36,451 --> 01:22:40,288
Give it to me, baby ! Ha ha ! Just like we used to do ! Come on !

978
01:22:43,959 --> 01:22:46,461
[ Thud ]

979
01:22:48,196 --> 01:22:50,065
[ All Screaming ]

980
01:22:53,468 --> 01:22:57,138
Moo ! Moo !

981
01:22:57,205 --> 01:22:59,641
What the hell are you doing ?

982
01:22:59,708 --> 01:23:03,211
[ Scott Laughs ] Moo !

983
01:23:03,278 --> 01:23:06,881
- [ Screaming ] - [ Scott Laughing ]

984
01:23:06,948 --> 01:23:10,752
- [ Growls ] - [ Gasping ]

985
01:23:10,819 --> 01:23:14,923
[ Scott Shouting, Whooping ] Hang on ! Yee-ha ! Here we go ! Touchdown !

986
01:23:31,005 --> 01:23:33,074
[ Sighs ] One point landing.

987
01:23:39,114 --> 01:23:41,716
We made it, baby. [ Crawford ] Okay.

988
01:23:41,783 --> 01:23:44,386
Let's get out of here as quick as we can.

989
01:23:44,452 --> 01:23:46,788
Jake, Commander, it's now or never.

990
01:23:49,057 --> 01:23:52,594
[ Computerized Voice ] Collision in five, four,

991
01:23:52,660 --> 01:23:56,398
three, two, one.

992
01:24:08,643 --> 01:24:11,913
Come on. Come on, right this way.

993
01:24:11,980 --> 01:24:15,717
Come on. Watch it. Watch it coming down here. You can really slip.

994
01:24:15,784 --> 01:24:18,353
Okay. You're all right. Come on.

995
01:24:28,029 --> 01:24:30,298
Commander, let's go !

996
01:25:08,403 --> 01:25:11,106
[ Knocking On Window ] [ Woman ] There's room in the back.

997
01:25:16,044 --> 01:25:18,880
[ Man ] Hey, let us in.

998
01:25:19,948 --> 01:25:22,116
Dad, you'll let them in, won't you ?

999
01:25:22,183 --> 01:25:26,688
We don't have the room for any of them. I wish we could.

1000
01:25:26,754 --> 01:25:29,124
What about the children ?

1001
01:25:31,292 --> 01:25:35,463
Just hold on. We're almost there.

1002
01:25:35,530 --> 01:25:39,801
[ Crowd ] Hey, come on. Pull over.

1003
01:26:14,536 --> 01:26:17,005
[ Crawford ] All right, steady.

1004
01:26:20,842 --> 01:26:24,279
[ Beeping ]

1005
01:26:24,345 --> 01:26:28,316
[ Computerized Voice ] Elevator now in transit. All right.

1006
01:26:28,383 --> 01:26:30,919
Let's go.

1007
01:26:50,338 --> 01:26:52,640
Just look forward.

1008
01:26:52,707 --> 01:26:55,410
What gives you the right to choose ?

1009
01:26:55,476 --> 01:26:57,812
Elevator security function activated.

1010
01:26:57,879 --> 01:27:01,616
Descension begins in 60 seconds. Quick. Quick.

1011
01:27:01,683 --> 01:27:05,053
- Come on. - I can't.

1012
01:27:05,119 --> 01:27:08,656
- What ? - I can't. It's not right.

1013
01:27:08,723 --> 01:27:10,792
Fifty seconds. What's not right ?

1014
01:27:10,858 --> 01:27:13,595
To live to see your child born ?

1015
01:27:13,661 --> 01:27:15,763
I'm not like you.

1016
01:27:15,830 --> 01:27:19,000
I don't believe in what you believe in. Forty seconds.

1017
01:27:19,067 --> 01:27:22,704
It doesn't matter what you believe if you don't exist.

1018
01:27:22,770 --> 01:27:25,907
Don't leave me.

1019
01:27:25,974 --> 01:27:29,677
